MBOMBELA – The long awaited State of the Province Address by Mpumalanga Premier, Refilwe Mtshweni-Tsipane was underway at the Mpumalanga Provincial Legislature today. Before Mtshweni-Tsipane outlined her plans for the province, guests walked the red carpet in their finery while traditional dancers performed to the appreciation of onlookers. ALSO READ:  This year’s Miss Mpumalanga finalists also graced the event in their stunning gowns as guests entered the building to hear what 2020 has in store for the province. 